    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>07</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2026-02-20</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2026-06-17T17:40:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Small Business Lending Fraud Prevention Act</strong></p><p>This bill requires Small Business Administration (SBA) employees who participate in the origination, review, or approval of&nbsp;SBA loans to certify in writing prior to such&nbsp;participation that the employee&nbsp;</p><ul><li>does not have any conflict of interest with respect to the loan,&nbsp;</li><li>will disclose any such conflict of interest arising after the certification is made, and</li><li>understands the requirements with respect to conflicts of interest applicable SBA employees.</li></ul><p>Under current law, federal employees must disclose financial conflicts of interest with respect to a particular matter and recuse themselves from such matter (with limited exceptions upon authorization from the employee's agency designee).</p><p>The SBA must issue regulations implementing the requirements of this bill.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
